England cricketers are used to getting a hard time Down Under – mainly at the crease.

But Eoin Morgan, the new captain of the nation’s one-day team, wasn’t prepared for the bouncer hurled at him yesterday from outside the ground.

Hours before he was due to lead out his side against Australia, the 28-year-old batsman found himself at the centre of a bizarre blackmail plot involving lurid sex messages and videos.

