Dublin-born Morgan, who was made captain of the one-day side last month, was due to lead the team out in Hobart at 3am, UK time, today. 

The ECB immediately told Scotland Yard of the blackmail plot after receiving two emails from Emery. UK detectives then tracked him down within 24 hours with the help of colleagues in Australia.

After meeting ECB officials and Australian police officers, Emery said he had made a mistake because he was in a ‘bad head space’. 

Speaking to the Melbourne-based Herald Sun newspaper, he said: ‘It’s done. It’s dealt with. I did the wrong thing in the wrong state of mind.

